-- в”Ђв”Ђ Clari в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Clari is an enterprise revenue orchestration platform that unifies pipeline forecasting, deal inspection, conversation intelligence, and sales execution for B2B teams.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription (custom quote)$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom pricing (quote-based)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$~900 employees (est., 2026)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Sunnyvale, California, US$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Clari: Enterprise Revenue Orchestration Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Clari is a revenue orchestration platform combining AI forecasting, pipeline inspection, and conversation intelligence for enterprise B2B sales teams.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Clari is an enterprise revenue operations platform, founded in 2013 by Andy Byrne and Venkat Rangan and headquartered in Sunnyvale, California. The company positions itself as a "revenue orchestration" platform that connects forecasting, pipeline management, deal execution, and go-to-market analytics into a single system used by enterprise sales, RevOps, and executive teams to run recurring revenue processes. Clari has raised significant venture funding over multiple rounds, including a $225 million Series F led by Blackstone and Silver Lake in January 2022 that valued the company at roughly $2.6 billion, and industry estimates put its annual recurring revenue in the hundreds of millions of dollars with roughly 1,500+ enterprise customers as of the mid-2020s. The product is organized into several modules that can be purchased together or, in some cases, separately: Clari Forecast (the original core product) provides AI-assisted revenue forecasting, pipeline inspection, and deal-risk scoring pulled from CRM and email/calendar data; Clari Copilot (formerly Wingman, acquired by Clari) adds conversation intelligence, call recording, transcription, and AI-generated coaching and deal insights from sales calls; Clari Align supports mutual action plans and buyer-seller collaboration workspaces to keep complex deals on track; and Clari Groove (from Clari's acquisition of sales-engagement platform Groove) adds email/call cadences and outbound automation. Clari does not publish self-serve pricing; every deployment is a custom, quote-based enterprise sale that depends on which modules are purchased, seat count, and negotiated terms, with third-party analyses estimating typical per-user costs in roughly the $60-$125/user/month range per module (and combined-stack costs in the $200-$310/user/month range for large deployments), plus separate implementation and professional-services fees that can run from roughly $15,000 to $75,000 for enterprise rollouts. Clari integrates with major CRM systems (principally Salesforce), email and calendar platforms, and various sales-engagement and communication tools, and it is built for large sales organizations rather than solo sellers or small teams вЂ” the platform's core value proposition is giving revenue leaders a single, always-current view of pipeline health and forecast accuracy that would otherwise be assembled manually from spreadsheets and disparate CRM reports. Because pricing and implementation scope are highly variable and negotiated per account, prospective buyers typically need to go through a sales and demo process with Clari directly to get an accurate quote, and the platform is generally evaluated against competitors such as Gong, Salesforce (via Sales Cloud/Einstein), Aviso, and BoostUp in the revenue-intelligence and forecasting category.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '6c40226a-eb4f-4492-897b-fa93c0ac4f4c';

